Package cs2030.simulator

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ServerID
    This interface holds the ServerID information of a Server.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArriveEvent
    This ArrivalEvent that handles the logic of receiving a customer that arrives.
    Customer
    This abstract class encapsulates the customer information and act as a parent class to GreedyCustomer and TypicalCustomer classes.
    CustomerComparator
    This class is to create a comparison criteria for customers.
    DoneEvent
    This DoneEvent that handles the logic of the completion of a service to a customer by the server.
    Event
    This abstract class enforces polymorphism, whereby every event subclasses: (i) ArriveEvent, (ii) ServedEvent, (iii) WaitsEvent, (iv) LeavesEvent, (v) DoneEvent, (vi) ServerRestEvent and (vii) ServerBackEvent, inherits from this Event class.
    EventComparator
    This class is to create a comparison criteria for events.
    EventManager
    This class handles the sequence of event executions.
    GreedyCustomer
    This class holds the GreedyCustomer information .
    HumanServer
    This class encapsulates the creation of a HumanServer, and that it goes to rest.
    LeavesEvent
    This LeavesEvent that handles the logic of a customer that leaves without being served.
    RandomGenerator  
    SelfCheckOut
    This class encapsulates the creation of a Self-Checkout Counter, and that it does not rest.
    ServedEvent
    This ServedEvent that handles the logic of the server serving a customer.
    Server
    This abstract class redirects the service of the customers according to their availability.
    ServerBackEvent
    ServerBackEvent stimulates the act of server getting back from rest.
    ServerRestEvent
    ServerRestEvent stimulates the act of server getting rest when the value generated from the genRandomRest() in RandomGenerated class is less than the probability of resting.
    Statistics
    This class encapsulates the calculation of server counter, leave counter and total waiting time of the customers.
    TypicalCustomer
    This class holds the TypicalCustomer information .
    WaitsEvent
    This WaitsEvent that handles the logic of the customer waiting to be served and there is vacancy in the server's queue to wait.
